## What LTX Does Well (for this show)

- Atmospheric footage with fog, light, and environmental drift
- Subtle character motion from good guidance frames — micro-gestures, shifts in weight, breathing
- Cinematic camera language — shallow DOF, film grain texture, naturalistic lighting
- Pacing and stillness — it can hold a shot without inventing unnecessary motion
- Audio ambience — room tone, city sounds, environmental texture

## What LTX Does Poorly (avoid or work around)

| Problem | Workaround |
|---------|------------|
| Readable text on screen | Composite text in post. Never rely on LTX to render the clinic log cards, terminal text, or any UI. |
| Character consistency across shots | Use Leonardo keyframes as guidance frames. Same seed + same prompt ≠ same character. |
| Complex multi-character choreography | Keep to one primary character per clip. Cut between angles rather than staging two people in motion simultaneously. |
| Stop-motion or clay texture | Will smooth into generic animation. Use ComfyUI for the mythology layer. |
| Sharp transitions or cuts within a single generation | LTX generates continuous motion. Hard cuts need to happen in editing, not in the prompt. |
| Very long holds (>8s of near-stillness) | Model tends to invent motion to fill time. Generate shorter clips and loop/extend in post. |
| Specific hand gestures or finger positions | Hands remain a weak point. Frame around them — medium shots hide hand artifacts. |

## Duration Guidance for Scene Types

| Scene Type | Recommended Duration | Why |
|------------|---------------------|-----|
| City Breath | 3–5s | Short atmospheric holds. Extend in post if needed. Longer gens drift. |
| Kitchen ambient (no dialogue) | 5–8s | Enough for a single beat of character behavior. |
| Dialogue beat | 5–8s | One exchange per clip. Break longer dialogue across multiple gens. |
| Emotional peak / silence | 4–6s | Restraint. Don't let the model fill silence with invented action. |
| Transition / interstitial | 2–3s | Bus, fog, hallway. Quick punctuation. |

